# Common React Patterns

## Page with API Data

```jsx
function Blog() {
  const { posts, loading, error } = useBlogPosts();
  if (loading) return <BlogSkeleton />;
  if (error) return <BlogError message={error} />;
  return (
    <>
      <BlogHero count={posts.length} />
      <BlogList posts={posts} />
    </>
  );
}
```

## Modal with Escape Key

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  const handleEsc = (e) => e.key === 'Escape' && onClose();
  if (isOpen) window.addEventListener('keydown', handleEsc);
  return () => window.removeEventListener('keydown', handleEsc);
}, [isOpen, onClose]);
```

## Form Handling

- Use `formData` state and `handleChange` for controlled inputs
- Track `status`: `idle` | `submitting` | `success` | `error`
- Disable submit button when `status === 'submitting'`
- Show success/error feedback

## Error Boundary for Data Fetching

Wrap data-fetching sections so one failed fetch doesn't crash the page:

```jsx
class ErrorBoundary extends Component {
  state = { hasError: false };
  static getDerivedStateFromError() { return { hasError: true }; }
  render() {
    if (this.state.hasError) return <div>Something went wrong.</div>;
    return this.props.children;
  }
}
// Usage: <ErrorBoundary><Blog /></ErrorBoundary>
```

## Clean Code

- Prefer `className` over inline `style` (use `style` only for dynamic values)
- Props for 1–2 levels; Context for 3+ or global data
- Keep components small; split if over ~150 lines
